Human Beta-globin Gene (HBB)

The HBB gene encodes the beta chain of hemoglobin, the protein responsible for oxygen transport in blood. Mutations in this gene are associated with disorders such as sickle cell anemia and beta-thalassemia.

This sequence is widely used in mutation analysis, PCR primer design, and comparative genomics studies. It is an excellent model for studying inherited genetic diseases and nucleotide variations.
